.TH MKCD 1 "2025-06-19" "scriptorium" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mkcd \- create directory and change into it
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mkcd
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.RI [ mkdir_options... ]
.I directory_name
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mkcd
creates a directory and immediately changes into it. It accepts and forwards
all options that
.BR mkdir (1)
accepts, making it a drop-in replacement that also changes to the created directory.

The directory name should be the last argument, with all mkdir options preceding it.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help message for mkcd (does not forward to mkdir --help)
.PP
All other options are forwarded directly to
.BR mkdir (1).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
mkcd -p projects/new-app
Creates the directory structure and changes into new-app
.TP
mkcd -v -m 755 temp
Creates temp directory with mode 755 and verbose output
.TP
mkcd --mode=700 private-dir
Creates directory with restrictive permissions using mkdir
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success, 1 on error from either mkdir or cd operations.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mkdir (1),
.BR cd (1),
.BR command (1)
